---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('curvature');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Definition</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					Possibility space has a geometry — and it shapes tension.
				</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Curvature</strong> is the warping of what seems possible: near or far, inevitable or unthinkable. It arises from the Identity Stem, accumulated Mass, and coherent Vision. It changes the geometry of options before any external force acts.
				</p>
				<p>
					A weak or diffuse identity leaves a nearly flat field — every path feels equally available and equally empty. A high-mass, directed stem bends the field so some trajectories feel natural while others require enormous effort.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Curvature and Tension</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55 mb-6">
					Curvature directly modulates the tension an identity experiences:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-5 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension amplification:</strong> Strong curvature makes certain paths feel almost inevitable and others almost impossible. This intensifies the experienced tension between what is desired and what feels accessible.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension reduction / channeling:</strong> Well-aligned curvature can reduce destructive tension by making productive paths feel natural and low-resistance.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Feedback loop:</strong> Mass and Rotation change curvature. Changed curvature then alters the tension field acting back on the identity. This is one of the primary ways an identity can consciously influence its own Spannung.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Distinction</div>
				<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">Curvature ≠ Gravitation</h2>
				<div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
					<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-6">
						<div class="mb-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/35">Curvature</div>
						<p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
							Shape of the distortion: the geometry of possibility for <em class="not-italic text-white/75">this</em> identity. It directly shapes the tension the identity itself experiences.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-6">
						<div class="mb-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/35">Gravitation</div>
						<p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
							What that bend does to <em class="not-italic text-white/75">others</em>: attraction between identities and the tension this interaction creates.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Engineering</div>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering work:</strong> Make the well intentional. If curvature is accidental (unexamined fears, borrowed goals, reactive denseness), we systematically misread near and far and waste force on paths that increase destructive tension instead of productive tension.
				</p>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6">
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/40 mb-3">Practical prompts</div>
					<ul class="space-y-3 text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<li>Which options currently feel “naturally near,” and is that proximity created by my vision or by inherited pressure?</li>
						<li>What deliberate curvature would reduce destructive tension and increase access to productive tension in the next 6–12 months?</li>
						<li>Where am I currently fighting against curvature I myself have created through past Mass and Rotation?</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="curvature" />
	</main>
</Layout>
